title: The_Last_Command_(1928)_Criterion_DVDRip_tsantilas
description:
The Last Command is a 1928 silent film directed by Josef von Sternberg. Star Emil Jannings won the very first Academy Award for Best Actor in a Leading Role for his performances in this film and The Way of All Flesh, the only year that multiple roles were considered. 

Plot: 

A decorated, aristocratic Czarist General (Emil Jannings) is reduced to penury after the collapse of Imperial Russia. An old adversary (William Powell), now a successful director hires the general to re-enact the revolution which deposed him.
